Our in-room safe wasn't working properly, but that was corrected while we went out for an afternoon exploration of Toronto.	Excellent rate of 3 nights for the price of 2 provided a huge room with ample storage facilities, Plasma TV and safe.	This Marriott was also within walking distance of the Toronto subway, and the walk was well-lit and safe.	I understand that for safety reasons the alarm was necessary, but did not understand why the annoucements continued every 5 minutes advising that they were looking into the matter and would provide further information later.	There was a safe large enough to fit my laptop in, something I always struggle with at other hotels.